==English==

===Etymology===
Greek ''[[kilo-]]'' + [[metre]] <!--or the SI prefix "kilo-" + metre, or a calque of the French? -->

===Pronunciation===
''American English'' - (IPA) /kɪləmiɾɚ/

===Alternative spellings===
*(''British, Canadian, etc.'') [[kilometre]]

===Noun===
'''kilometer''' (''US spelling''; ''plural'' '''[[kilometers]]''')
# An [[SI#Abbreviation|SI]]/MKS unit of measure equal to one thousand [[meter]]s.

====Symbol====
*[[km]] (''official [[SI]] symbol''), [[Km]] (''chiefly American, in non-scientific usage, such as in road signs'')

